\begin_layout Abstract
This work presents a study about possible uses of panoramic images in augmented
 reality aplications for mobile devices as cellphones and tablets.
 It will be explained concepts as augmented reality, QR code and panoramic
 images.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
It aims for studying means to merge information from real world, where we,
 human beings, are inserted with data produced or acquired using computers.
 These informations may be localization data from a GPS source, comments,
 sounds or images from internet source or even tridimensional elements modeled
 in a computer software.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Unlike most approaches made in the field of mobile augmented reality, this
 study is based on the use of previously photographed images instead of
 the natural vision of the environment provided by the camera of any device.
 The proposal is to replace the environment's real image, which could be
 seen through the camera of any mobile device, with a panoramic image taken
 previously on that same environment.
\end_layout

